steps.instruction:
### Mixing
- Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl
- Mix everything till a sticky rough dough forms
    - If using a mixer use a beater blade on medium speed for 30 to 60 seconds
    - If you don't have a mixer use a big spoon or a dough whisk till everything is combined

### Let It Rise
- Keep the dough in at least a 6 quart container and cover it with plastic wrap
- Let the dough rise for at least 2 hours in room temperature
    - If you're pressed for time you can skip this step
- Then transfer the dough to the fridge to rise for an additional 2 hours
    - You can keep the dough in the fridge for up to 7 days
    - The longer you keep the dough in the fridge, the tangier it will get. At day 7 it will taste like sourdough

### Forming
- Sprinkle flour over the top of the dough
- Sprinkle flour onto a work surface
- Try to grab 1/4 to 1/3 of the dough
    - Or grab a 14 to 19 ounce piece if you have a scale
- Put the sticky dough on a floured work surface
- Work the dough to form a ball
- Place the loaf onto a piece of parchment paper
    - If you're **NOT** using a baking stone, place it onto a lightly greased parchment-lined baking sheet
- Sift a light coating of flour over the top

### Baking
- Let the loaf reach room temperature (about 60 minutes)
    - Preheat your oven to 450F some time while the dough is warming back up
    - If you're using a baking stone put the stone in the middle rack of the oven and then put a **metal** pan on the bottom rack
- When you're ready to bake take a sharp knife and slash the bread 2 or 3 times about 1/2" deep
- Place the bread in the oven
    - If using a baking stone put it on that in the middle rack
    - If you're using a pan pour about 1 cup of water into it and quickly close the door
- Bake for 25 to 35 minutes
